</md></sn><sn><md>### Pressure of the Atmosphere from Barometer{.text-center}

We all know that,

$$ P = \frac{F}{A} \quad \text{(eq1)} $$

force per unit area.

Now,$F = mg$ ,here m is the mass of the barometer upto 76cm.

$$ \rho = \frac{m}{v}  $$
$$ m = \rho v  $$

Now $F = mg$ or $F = \rho v$,substituting F in eq1

$$ P = \frac{\rho vg}{A} $$

$$ P = \frac{\rho Ahg}{A} $$

$$ P = \rho h g $$

$$ P = 13.6 \times 76 \times 980 $$

$$ P = 1.0136\times10^6 dynes/cm^2 $$

